{ [%cal Gb7b5,Gf6d5,Gc6d5,Ga7a5,Ga5a4,Rd8a5,Rf8e8,Ra8d8,Ra8c8]black has reached his ideal setup. Here's a list of the possible plans: 1. To push c5 while being careful that the opening of the position after either dc5 or d5 is good for him. 2. To play Nd5 looking for exchanges, if white takes Nd5 then black takes with the c-pawn and starts a minority attack on the queenside. 3. To gain space on the queenside by a5-a4. To play Qa5 in order to connect the rooks, which will come to e8,d8 or c8, depending on circumstances. }
